result.execSummary:
The defendant Misael Olmos Garcia was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "B", Domestic Abuse Surcharge], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A", Domestic Abuse Surcharge], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

The defendant enters a plea of Guilty to counts 1 and 5. The Court finds the Defendant Guilty of counts 1 and 5 and directs a JOC be entered on both counts 1 and 5. The Court dismisses and reads in remaining counts. Count 1 and 5 are to be a withheld sentence for a period of 2 years with the conditions being Defendant shall cooperate with, participate in, and successfully complete evaluations, treatment, Alcohol and drug classes, Domestic Violence classes, Co-Parenting classes  and counseling deemed appropriate by Agent.
